[SPEAKER_03]: I had a great accent, but I didn't know anything about subjunctive.

174
00:22:28,975 --> 00:22:34,177
[SPEAKER_03]: I didn't know anything about conditional, but I can work present and past tense, okay?

175
00:22:34,657 --> 00:22:38,298
[SPEAKER_03]: And that's exactly what I did then, okay?

176
00:22:38,498 --> 00:22:42,840
[SPEAKER_03]: I turned the interview around to present and past tense.

177
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:45,521
[SPEAKER_03]: With my accent.

178
00:22:46,341 --> 00:22:49,202
[SPEAKER_03]: And then he said, walk across the room.

179
00:22:51,468 --> 00:22:52,289
[SPEAKER_03]: I knew how to walk.

180
00:22:53,911 --> 00:22:55,333
[SPEAKER_03]: So I walked across the room.

181
00:22:56,034 --> 00:22:59,158
[SPEAKER_03]: And then he said, well, thank you very much, Ms.

182
00:22:59,318 --> 00:22:59,638
[SPEAKER_03]: Nutt.

183
00:23:01,621 --> 00:23:03,143
[SPEAKER_03]: We will get in touch with you.

184
00:23:03,924 --> 00:23:07,108
[SPEAKER_03]: He said, if you're selected to go to the next level,

